<div class="container-fluid">
	<h1>About My Family and Me</h1>
<p>Well, about me, I am a jack of all trades, but mostly I am looking for a more simple life than I've already lived.  This simpler life came in the form of backyard gardens and the dream of owning property that would produce food and income opportunities for ouselves, children, and neighbors.  This opportunity is becoming a reality as we are close to closing on a nearly 80 acre lot with wonderful home.  The Food for My Neighbors LLC land offers an appple orchard, ample garden space, hardwood maples for syrup or lumber.  The land houses three deer blinds on deer migration routes along with opportunity for hunting bear and fishing in the nearby Fox River.</p>

<p>This is truely the chance of a lifetime home for my family.  We have all worked hard, sacrificing for this moment.  We are truely blessed to be able to reap what we have sewn and share it with all of you.</p>

<p>What was the hecktic life before this, you wonder?  I am an educator at heart and was by trade for five years.  Although I do love to teach and open minds to the wonders of the world, I felt I needed a different platform in which to utillize my talents.  This website and my farm will be my new platform.  Next year my dear husband and I plan to have our farm partner with the schools in our area for a few educational field trips.  This is just in the planning stages, but wow, what an amazing asset organic education could be to our schools and community.</p>

<p>My family consists of my husband, our two young children, a future puppy, and myself.  Including all the bugs and animals in the world and imaganative world, that makes quite a few of us!</p>
